UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Jose Luis AGUILAR-GARZA, Jr., also known as Luis Garza, Jr., Defendant-Appellant. No. 03-40361.

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 10, 2003. James Lee Turner, Assistant US Attorney, US Attorney’s Office, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Jose Luis Aguilar-Garza, Jr., pro se, Houston, TX, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before DAVIS, EMILIO M. GARZA, and DENNIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.*

Court-appointed counsel for Jose Luis Aguilar-Garza, Jr., has moved for leave to *901withdraw and has filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Aguilar has not filed a response to the motion. Our review of the brief filed by counsel and of the record discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, the motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
